This time piece was made to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the silver Snoopy award, which was awarded by NASA astronauts in 1970 in honor of the contribution of Omega to space exploration, including Apollo 13.





The blue nylon fabric strap is made of 42 mm stainless steel case, and the Apollo 13 track is embossed on the lining of the strap. The silver dial includes blue PVD index and needle, and a blue sub dial at 9 o'clock has embossed silver medallion with a Snoopy.





The back side of the moon that uses the microstructure metal of the sapphire crystal glass is drawn in the case back which adopted the nade rock system. The Snoopy on the command machine ship is equipped with a magic hand that is rotated when the chronograph function is used. On the back side, there is a disk that has the earth, and it rotates in one minute in conjunction with the small size of the clock.





In the case back, Apollo 13 and Omega's silver \Snoopy awards\" are marked as black. Blue ceramic [ZrO2] bezel ring features a tachymeter scale painted with white enamel. This time piece
